y, the nature of which continues to be disputed, particularly with regard to World War II. The authors of History, Memory, and Politics in Postwar Japan explore Japan's historical narratives, and their impact on both domestic politics and diplomatic relations, as they have evolved from 1946 to the present. Presenting the results of more than a decade of collaborative research, their book is a rich contribution to our understanding not only of Japanese politics, but also of how the historical narratives that we embrace have far-reaching consequences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aMemoryzJapan. 0aMemory-Japan. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Asian.2bisacsh1 aJun’ya, Nishino, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaoru, Iokibe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaoru, Iokibe, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKazuo, Komiya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKazuo, Komiya, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRyōta, Murai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShin, Kawashima, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSusumu, Satō, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaizō, Miyagi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTomoki, Takeda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTsuneo, Watanabe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYoshitoshi, Taira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYūichi, Hosoya , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aYūichi, Hosoya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBoo